    { "type": "paragraph", "children": [{ "text": "" }] },
    { "type": "heading-two", "children": [{ "text": "" }] },
    {
      "type": "heading-one",
      "children": [{ "text": "Create Tension, Then Give Relief" }]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        { "text": "Remember the idea of ‚Äúresolution‚Äù we talked about? The way G7 wants to rush home to C " },
        { "text": "/post/basic/harmony-II#harmony-5-1 ", "link": true },
        {
          "text": " is the same principle‚Äîjust upgraded. Modal interchange is simply the next level."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "In the last chapter we said, ‚ÄúIf you eat nothing but sweet cake, you get sick of it; a little bitter matcha resets the palate.‚Äù Interchange is one of those matcha powders‚Äîfirst a surprise, then a return home, and the familiar tastes sweeter than ever."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Pastry chefs do the same: a dusting of bitter cocoa or matcha, a layer of tart berry jam‚Äîanything to wake the taste buds before the sugary comfort returns. The diatonic notes are the ‚Äúcake‚Äù; the foreign notes are the ‚Äúmatcha.‚Äù"
        }
      ]
    },
    { "type": "paragraph", "children": [{ "text": "" }] },
    { "type": "heading-one", "children": [{ "text": "" }] },
    { "type": "heading-one", "children": [{ "text": "More Flavor Experiments" }] },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        { "text": "Let‚Äôs try another ‚Äúseasoning.‚Äù Here is a C-major 4-3-6-1 progression:" }
      ]
    },
