          { "instrument": "drum", "notes": [] }
        ],
        "timeLength": 10,
        "currentTrack": "piano",
        "bpm": 80,
        "keyboardOctave": 4
      },
      "children": [{ "text": "" }]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Right before IV, we fake a mini ‚Äú5-1 in F major‚Äù: treat Fmaj as a temporary I. The V of F is C7 (count it on the keyboard). Slip C7 in front of Fmaj and‚Äîvoil√†‚Äîan local 5-1 cadence."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Inside the home key of C major this pocket feels fresh‚Äîpartly outside, yet perfectly logical because it follows the same tension-release grammar:"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
