    },
    { "type": "paragraph", "children": [{ "text": "" }] },
    { "type": "heading-three", "children": [{ "text": "" }] },
    { "type": "heading-one", "children": [{ "text": "More Classic ‚ÄúSeasonings‚Äù" }] },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [{ "text": "‚Ä¢ ‚ÄúTritone Substitution‚Äù: replace G7 with Db7" }]
    },
    { "type": "paragraph", "children": [{ "text": "" }] },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [{ "text": "Compare the two chord tones:" }]
    },
    { "type": "paragraph", "children": [{ "text": "G7: G B D F" }] },
    { "type": "paragraph", "children": [{ "text": "Db7: Db F Ab B (Cb)" }] },
    { "type": "paragraph", "children": [{ "text": "" }] },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "First, understand that a tritone‚Äîtwo notes exactly six semitones apart‚Äîsounds terribly tense and begs for resolution. Listen:"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "roll",
      "id": "3d40d276-06e6-4a89-9fba-6ac0003113f2",
