      "children": [{ "text": "" }]
    },
    { "type": "paragraph", "children": [{ "text": "" }] },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Much of a dominant chord‚Äôs unrest comes from this interval. It aches to collapse into the tonic."
        }
      ]
    },
    { "type": "paragraph", "children": [{ "text": "" }] },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Now notice: both G7 and Db7 contain the same tritone, just flipped:"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [{ "text": "G7: 3rd B and 7th F ‚Üí B‚ÜîF" }]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [{ "text": "Db7: 3rd F and 7th Cb(=B) ‚Üí F‚ÜîB" }]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [{ "text": "Same pair, mirror image." }]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        { "text": "That B‚ÜîF is the most unstable, ‚Äúmust-return-to-C‚Äù sound around." }
      ]
    },
    { "type": "paragraph", "children": [{ "text": "" }] },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
